If you choose a [viewing mode|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/GH/Using+Planning+Board+Modes] other than 'version' on the planning board and then attempt to edit the version of any issue cards the following error is thrown:
!versionerror.png!

Replicated on Atlassian OnDemand with JIRA 5.1.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-5394].
  {panel}

*Investigation result:* the problematic data is on JAC, specifically in the JIRA project. For example, JRA-77 has Change History entries in the database with no Change Items associated to them. This causes code to blow up.

Go [here|https://jira.atlassian.com/secure/RapidBoard.jspa?rapidView=236&selectedIssue=JRA-28607]
Then go [here|https://jira.atlassian.com/secure/VersionBoard.jspa]

